main event: A civilian reported seeing one unidentified object in Duluth, Minnesota on 23 August 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed visually but no photographs or physical evidence were provided., The witness's observation has been classified as insufficient data for evaluation., Lt. Stoecker noted limited information on sightings in the Duluth area from the local air force base., The document referenced previous communications about UFO sightings in the region., The object was reported to have been high and stationary before it disappeared by flying straight up.
